snippet.textDisplay:
Im Gonna take this time to talk about how I broke up me and my best friends because I need to get myself over it. Amy, Beth, Charlie and Daisy were best friends with me in year 9 and in yr 10, Daisy and Charlie had an argument about Daisys boyfriend and then they ended their friendship. Seriously they were the bestest of friends and then they just weren't. After this Amy and Beth were still friends with Charlie and I spoke to Daisy still even though it was a bit wierd I still missed her.

Fast forward to yr12 and then I see Daisy in the common room and she's here, we catch up a bit and basically I told her about the fact that Amy Beth and Charlie had had conversations about her and her boyfriend in the past. I didn't specifically remember how many of them there were and at the time I didn't think about how stupid it was to tell her something that Amy, Beth and Charlie told me in confidence of privacy but I mean I literally just said what I said in response to a question asked. It may be disgusting to some people to do that and I'm gonna have to find a way to do it in the future with more respect for both people.

3months later, I'm told by Daisy that Charlie was screen recording snaps of Daisy to send to people and talk bad about so she went up to Charlie and confronted her. Of course Charlie was terribly scared by the threat of being expelled because there was a chance of being in a fight with Daisy but then she called me to try and understand what I told her to actually get Daisy so angry at Charlie. I told her that I told daisy about conversations that they had about Daisys bf but at the same time there were less than 5 that I could count at the time in the whole time up until this happened so me telling Daisy about that may have been an overexaggeration on my part. After that they made it quite explicit how they wanted me out of their life. Betrayal doesn't go down with anyone I guess huh? Guess it really shouldn't tho tbh.

Nonetheless I am now here sitting in front of my computer 3months later with no best friends because of a mistake I made that I still need to stop thinking about and the fact I got them even more angry at me by purposely hugging Amy a month later, following them around like a clown after they had a conversation with me trying to get me to apologise (which I completely failed at doing at that specific conversation for some sad reason) and followed them around as if they were ok with me.

The point of this? I have alot to learn if I still haven't moved on yet even though it's been a few months since it happened and I needed to vent but also the fact that they have broken up and literally they both were so adult about it and there wasn't any big scandal or affair, it's so commendable that they can do that and live and continue living or at least try to. It's just incredible.
